{"TopicId":41712,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Would KSP run on a raspberry pi?","CreatedByName":"Marknate24","CreatedById":74651,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-09T02:09:16Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Marknate24","CreatedById":74651,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-09T02:09:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI know that steam has a Linux version of KSP, so would the raspberry pi b\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlternNocturn","CreatedById":17872,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-09T02:49:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ENo. KSP calculates physics on the CPU and the Raspberry Pi doesn\u0027t have nearly the computing power.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rockhem","CreatedById":57141,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-09T02:59:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIf you cluster some raspberry pi\u0027s togehter you should be able to do it.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlternNocturn","CreatedById":17872,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-09T03:21:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rockhem\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Rockhem\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EIf you cluster some raspberry pi\u0027s togehter you should be able to do it.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYou can do that!?! O_O\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rockhem","CreatedById":57141,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-09T03:27:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYeah i remember seeing someone run truly intense games that my computer barely scrapes along on a raspberry pi cluster.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Moon Goddess","CreatedById":57446,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-09T03:28:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI know that Unity has been ported to ARM but has KSP?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Marknate24","CreatedById":74651,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-09T10:15:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Moon Goddess\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Moon Goddess\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EI know that Unity has been ported to ARM but has KSP?\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI don\u0027t know, if steam is able to run then ksp should be up for download.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Marknate24","CreatedById":74651,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-09T10:20:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AlternNocturn\u0022 data-cite=\u0022AlternNocturn\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EYou can do that!?! O_O\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.southampton.ac.uk/mediacentre/features/raspberry_pi_supercomputer.shtml\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.southampton.ac.uk/mediacentre/features/raspberry_pi_supercomputer.shtml\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis guy combined 64 rpis\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"skykooler","CreatedById":60459,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-09T12:59:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Moon Goddess\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Moon Goddess\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EI know that Unity has been ported to ARM but has KSP?\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENo. KSP would need at the very least a recompile to run on ARM, and only Squad could do that.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlso, a Raspberry Pi doesn\u0027t have nearly enough CPU power, and clustering them wouldn\u0027t help at all because KSP still can\u0027t use multiple cores.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lazarus1024","CreatedById":65276,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-09T14:16:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EExactly, you can\u0027t cluster as KSP can\u0027t multithread. So...no, you couldn\u0027t. Even if you recompiled for ARM I doubt it would run. We are talking something with less compute power than my phone...which has roughly 1/5th the compute power of my laptop. I think it would crash and burn BADLY. Okay...technically it might actually be able to run, but I doubt you\u0027d manage more than maybe 2-3FPS even with something like a 3 part rocket.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Van Disaster","CreatedById":58876,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-09T14:39:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ERPI is roughly equivalent to a 300Mhz Pentium, I think. Seems unlikely...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWould be fun if you could run a ship on one \u0026amp; cluster a bunch, use a more powerful box for a graphical head.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JakeGrey","CreatedById":61242,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-09T15:00:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Van Disaster\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Van Disaster\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003ERPI is roughly equivalent to a 300Mhz Pentium, I think.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWith a GPU roughly equivalent to an Xbox plugged into it, yeah. I\u0027m pretty sure an RPi could handle the graphics side, but the physics calcs? Well, maybe once we\u0027re in the beta phase and Squad are in a position to do some systematic optimisation.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Danerdygeek","CreatedById":78320,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-09T23:53:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYou could if you used multiple pi\u0027s and linked them up to a controller unit (don\u0027t actually know what they are called), It\u0027s basically a not so super super computer! \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MK3424","CreatedById":19932,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T22:48:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA raspberry Pi 2 might be powerfull enough....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NeMeSiS","CreatedById":5379,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T22:50:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222367293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002241712\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453070895\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002219932\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MK3424\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, MK3424 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA raspberry Pi 2 might be powerfull enough....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot even close. KSP wouldn\u0027t run properly on a phone, and a Raspberry Pi (2) doesn\u0027t even come close to that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-17T22:50:55Z\u0022 title=\u002201/17/2016 10:50  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 17, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by NeMeSiS\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlamoVampire","CreatedById":78020,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T23:04:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/19932-mk3424/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002219932\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/19932-mk3424/\u0022\u003E@MK3424\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/5379-nemesis/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u00225379\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/5379-nemesis/\u0022\u003E@NeMeSiS\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Guys 2 things, 1. Ksp runs on pumpkin pie and 2. Epic necrothreading!\n\u003C/p